From d68a55fe078d9992f6b4952385078d0d5f0c71f4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sat, 7 Mar 2026 16:39:09 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: yield ambient tick immediately when operator messages
 arrive mid-tick
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The orientation LLM call (and potentially journal/disposition LLM calls)
inside run_ambient_tick can take 5-30+ seconds to complete. If a user sends
a message while this is running, the agent would not process it until the
entire ambient tick finished — adding multi-second latency to every response
that arrives during an ambient cycle.

Add has_pending_operator_messages() checks at two points:
  1. After maybe_update_orientation() returns — before execute_disposition
     (which may issue another LLM call for journaling)
  2. After execute_disposition() — before self-directive and heartbeat

When pending messages are found, the function returns early with the
computed orientation so the caller can still use it for tick-duration
calculation. The engaged loop on the next iteration picks up the messages
immediately without sleeping.

https://claude.ai/code/session_01V9hxaXY8jJ1S5ABTe8bBDo
---
 src/agent/mod.rs | 14 ++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 14 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/agent/mod.rs b/src/agent/mod.rs
index 273cf71..01d6a3a 100644
--- a/src/agent/mod.rs
+++ b/src/agent/mod.rs
@@ -2650,6 +2650,15 @@ impl Agent {
 
         let previous_orientation = self.last_orientation.read().await.clone();
         let orientation = self.maybe_update_orientation(pending_events).await;
+
+        // The orientation LLM call can take 5-30+ seconds. Check again for operator
+        // messages that may have arrived while it was running. If any are pending,
+        // skip all further ambient work (disposition, journal, heartbeat, social) so the
+        // engaged loop can handle them immediately on the next iteration.
+        if self.has_pending_operator_messages().await {
+            return orientation;
+        }
+
         if let Some(ref orientation) = orientation {
             self.execute_disposition(
                 &config_snapshot,
@@ -2660,6 +2669,11 @@ impl Agent {
             .await;
         }
 
+        // Re-check after execute_disposition (may include a journal LLM call).
+        if self.has_pending_operator_messages().await {
+            return orientation;
+        }
+
         self.maybe_run_self_directive(&config_snapshot, pending_events)
             .await;
 
